<subSubSection id="C3276BD27A72FF83FF0A508087805042" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8238597A72FF83FF0A508087805042" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B949E44B7A72FF83FF0A5080866C51EE" bold="true" box="[199,315,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3D43DA7A72FF83FE885080868451EE" authorityName="Montandon" authorityYear="1907" box="[325,467,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Apennocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949E44B7A72FF83FE885080868451EE" box="[325,467,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Apennocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only genus among taxa allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D43DA7A72FF83FC6D5080835951EE" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[928,1038,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Germalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949E44B7A72FF83FC6D5080835951EE" box="[928,1038,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Germalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which wing polymorphism and a flightless morph is documented. This condition is associated with habitat permanency in Lygaeoidea (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC45A87A72FF83FA9450AC878751A6" author="Slater, J. A." pageId="3" pageNumber="288" pagination="217 - 229" refId="ref3677" refString="Slater, J. A. (1977) The incidence and evolutionary significance of wing polymorphism in lygaeid bugs with particular reference to those of South Africa. Biotropica, 9 (4), 217 - 229. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2388139" type="journal article" year="1977">Slater 1977</bibRefCitation>
) and relatively common in Afrotopical, Nearctic and Palaearctic representatives of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D43DA7A72FF83FB2F50C887855042" authority="Fallen, 1814" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1814" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Geocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949E44B7A72FF83FB2F50C8821E51A6" box="[1250,1353,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="288">Geocoris</emphasis>
Fallén, 1814
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
